    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-04T16:56:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-04T16:56:00-05:00" n="659"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d659">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2885</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Arnold</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-04T16:00:00-05:56">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 4, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11.15 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department circular, September 20, 6 p.m. Note received from the Foreign Office
                    states that the Government of Salvador being inspired in the most firm and
                    enthusiastic manner in the sentiments of the United States Government hereby
                    register their most explicit protest for the sufferings to which the Russian
                    citizens have been so cruelly subjected and to register [their] decision to
                    cooperate quickly in aid of whatever measures the Government of the United
                    States deems proper to take in the matter and in so far as it is possible for
                    Salvador to participate in the same morally and materially. Full text of note
                    follows by pouch.<note n="2" xml:id="d659fn2">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Arnold</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
